=======
Install
=======

You can get LapackDoc from __github__.  After cloning the repository compile
its `f77crash` tools and adjust your `PATH` environment variable:

  *--[SHELL(hide)]----------------------------------------------*
  |                                                             |
  |  rm -rf /tmp/demo/LapackDoc                                 |
  |  mkdir -p /tmp/demo                                         |
  |                                                             |
  *-------------------------------------------------------------*

  *--[SHELL]----------------------------------------------------*
  |                                                             |
  |  cd /tmp/demo                                               |
  |  git clone https://github.com/michael-lehn/LapackDoc.git    |
  |  cd LapackDoc                                               |
  |  cd f77crash                                                |
  |  make                                                       |
  |  cd ..                                                      |
  |  export PATH=$PATH:$PWD                                     |
  |  export LAPACKDOC=$PWD                                      |
  |                                                             |
  *-------------------------------------------------------------*

:links: github  ->   https://github.com/michael-lehn/LapackDoc
